PartitionA<V,E> - Class in org.jgrapht.experimental.decomposition
Implements PartitionA from 'Computing Cut-Based Hierarchical Decompositions in Almost linear time' by RŠcke, Shah, TŠubig (pages 4 - 10) The Algorithm receives a Graph g and partitions it into sets Z_i s.t. for every Z_i: |Z_i| <= 3/4 |E|.

performMatchingStepV2(SplitGraph<V, E>, Set<MatchedPair<SplitGraphVertex<V, E>>>) - Method in class org.jgrapht.experimental.decomposition.MatchingStep
Gets a fractional, partial matching and performs an averaging step (move flow vectors depending on the weight between a pair of matched vertices) ('right' computation: for 2 Matchings (a,c,w_1) , (b,c,w_2) f_c = (1 - w_1 - w_2) * f_c + w_1 * f_a + w_2 * f_b )
